import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='x', y='y')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between X and Y?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='x', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['x'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of X?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='y', kde=True, color='blue', bins=20)
    plt.axvline(data['y'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2)
    plt.legend(['Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['y'].median())], loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Y?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
